F/y/i -- The proposed Enron media position on the LNG vessel fire incident is 
set forth as an attachment below.  Enron PR is anticipating (and in fact may 
have received) a question or two from the international shipping press re the 
incident as it is well known in LNG and shipping circles that Enron recently 
signed a timecharter for the service of this vessel.  

We're still gathering info re the incident (the shipowner appears to be 
cooperating fully but still has significant access restrictions due to the 
pending investigation) and will relay any relevant info we receive.  We have 
asked for a copy of any official incident report when it is available.  To 
date, we have not received any communications regarding potential involvement 
in a claim.  Although it is always possible that we could be named, we are 
confirming with maritime counsel that our exposure under maritime and tort 
law in connection with this incident is slight, if any, as we had no 
involvement in or control over the shipyard operations and the vessel had not 
been delivered into service for Enron at the time of the incident. 

Stay tuned for more as things develop.

Kind regards,
Dan
